ShortDescription: Furnished Rooms in Large North Campus Area House Utilities Included
LongDescription:
Great location with close easy access to Cornell campus,  short walk no hills.

All utilities and internet included
Free laundry in the building
Two blocks to many bus routes
Free off street parking

Three floor house with 9 furnished bedrooms, living room, kitchen (two refrigerators, dishwasher), dining area and 3 baths.

10 or 12 month lease

Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups.  walking distance to Cornell  University.
Corner of Eddy St. & Buffalo St. 
- Aug., 2025
LongDescription:
Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups. 
Corner of Eddy and Buffalo Street. 
A well maintained large house. 
Walking distance to Cornell University.

All utilities and garbage disposal included.

Cleaning service provided for common areas. 
Laundry on premises.

Available 8/10/2024, 12 months lease. 

Pls TEXT: Sharon 929 538 9073 (cell);

ShortDescription: Recently renovated( see pictures) pet friendly,large 350 square foot studio apartment,with full kitchen and bath, 6 minutes to vet school.
LongDescription: Many veterinarian and grad students live here in this small quiet complex of 24 units. All have walk out access to a spacious 2.5 acre grounds located across the road from Fall creek. Trash, parking, water and sewer, professional  and courteous maintenance provided by the owner of 22 years, included in the rent on this updated studio apartment . Laundry on site , and bus service available. Rent w/o pets $820.00 mo, $845.00 with pets.

ShortDescription: Renovated House available near Campus AUG 2025

House available starting 8/8/2025 - 7/31/2026. 10 min walk to campus. Bus stop around corner. No smoking or pets. Accepting applications for groups of 6.

Includes:
- Furnished rooms with bed, dresser, desk
- Furnished living room and study room
- 2 renovated bathrooms 
- New kitchen appliances
- Free laundry in basement

Internet & utilities not included. Video tour available. Email for questions. More details: www.ferrisplacerentals.com

ShortDescription:
GEM OF A PLACE    NEAR THE VET SCHOOL
AVAILABLE April 1, 2025 
2 BDRM
LongDescription: The bottom part of a house with a separate entrance- light and bright and not at all basement-y. Newer kitchen and plenty of room. In a quiet, beautiful country setting near the state forest. Is well maintained and has a propane stove to keep you cozy in the winter, new washer and dryer and flooring. The apartment is centrally located: the Commons is nine miles; Dryden/TC3 is approximately six miles and Cornell is eight miles. Come make it your home. Non-smoking/vaping and pets upon approval.

ShortDescription: Large and Quiet 2 Bed 2.5 Bath in the Sapsucker Woods Neighborhood. Near Campus and Available For Spring Semester or Short Term Leases.
LongDescription:
Loft style 2 Bedroom, 2.5 bath Town homes with vaulted ceilings, fireplace, 1 car garage, central air, full basement with washer/dryer hook-ups. Modern and maintenance free town home living located in Ithaca with a wonderfully scenic and wooded area next to the bird Sanctuary. 


$2544/ month plus utilities. 


10 Sanctuary #2 - $2544.00 a month plus utilities

Contact office to schedule a viewing or to inquire about other Sanctuary units available!

ShortDescription: Lovely  1 BR plus study apartment in home; 5-7 minute walk  to Collegetown, Law School on Main Campus in family neighborhood. Perfect fo serious law student who hopes to make Law Journal!
LongDescription: Charming apt. i  5-7 minute walk to Cornell Law School in quiet Bryant Park/Belle Sherman neighborhood close to campus. Large eat in kitchen, full bath w/shower, spacious front room and second smaller bonus room, Perfect for law student. The house has an almost perfect track record for its tenants earning places on the Law Journal. If you want to succeed in your studies, live in a nice environment with landlord whom you know and trust to repair any problems as they arise, 224 Bryant is for you.

ShortDescription: Rooms available for 2025-2026 school year.  1-4 bedrooms available in fully furnished, recently renovated shared 5-bedroom home across the street from Campus.  Rent is $850 per month plus utilities.
LongDescription: Across the street from Cornell close to West Campus.  Property has been recently renovated (including central heating and air conditioning systems). Other details: 2 ½ baths (radiant floor heat), full kitchen (appliances including dishwasher), living room, dining room, washer and dryer, convenient 24 hr parking on street, plenty of storage space, backyard, bus stop across the street.

One of the best deals you can find in Ithaca.

ShortDescription: Beautiful Downtown Bedroom -SOON Avail Grad., PhD. Students/Professor. Same block with TCAT bus to Cornell, and Cascadilla Gorge. Walk path to Cornell. Only 2 blocks to Down Town! Furnished & Classy.
LongDescription:
Best located Historic Home in Ithaca for You & Your Family for lease. 
One of the first built homes in the city, this home was also once selected as the first Monastery in Ithaca for Tibetan Monks, while the separate upstairs apartment served as a yoga studio. 
Jacuzzi & updated bathrooms; Hard wood floors throughout, open kitchen and granite table dining, 3-common large spaces w/ beautiful furniture, expansive patio for entertaining with sound of the waterfalls behind you, and more!

ShortDescription:
Renting for 2025-26! 
Nice 3 bedroom, 1 bath apt with high ceilings, newer kitchen with dishwasher, open layout living & dining room, and full bath. Laundry in unit, built in storage shelves & more!
LongDescription:
3 Beds 1 Bath Apartment (starting Aug 2025). 331 N Geneva St, Ithaca. Great top floor and furnished.
Conveniently located! Minutes to Cornell (just below University Ave, less than 5 minutes from CU library & Barton Hall) and walking distance to Ithaca commons. Bus to Cornell & other areas also minutes away.

ShortDescription: BEAUTIFUL 5BR UNITS AVAILABLE FOR 2025-2026!!!
LongDescription: Stunning 5BR/2BA units still available for 2025-2026! These bright, spacious units were built just last year. They come fully furnished with double beds, desks, armoires, in unit laundry, stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, laminate flooring, custom tile in bathrooms, body sprayers, waterfall shower heads and LED mirrors. ShortDescription:
2025 SUMMER SUBLET - Ithaca Commons Private Room
Private a 3-bed-2-bath apartment. The monthly rent includes all utilities besides electricity. Indoor washer&dryer, furniture provided. Female only.
LongDescription: I am subletting this spacious, fully furnished apartment starting Summer 2025, and it’s perfectly situated in the heart of Downtown Ithaca at the Commons. You’ll be just a short walk from the best bars, cafes, and restaurants, with a bus stop conveniently across the street. Enjoy the convenience of in-door laundry and available parking. It also offers great amenities like 24/7 maintenance, internet, a secure entrance, and a rooftop terrace. If you're interested, reach out to st678@cornell.edu

ShortDescription: Medium-sized room is conveniently located on the first floor at the back of the house. It is adjacent to the bathroom and directly off the kitchen and back door.
LongDescription: This inviting medium-sized room is thoughtfully designed for comfort and convenience. It offers easy access to the bathroom and is directly adjacent to the kitchen, with the added benefit of discreet back door access for coming and going with ease. The room features tan hardwood floors and is equipped with a window unit and brand-new charcoal grey furniture, including a sleek queen-size bed and a matching dresser.

ShortDescription: Motivated sublet! Entire apartment in The Ithacan. 1 bed, 1 bath + office, furnished. Stainless steel, W/D, walk-in closet. Rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge. Available to June 2025.
LongDescription:
Avoid a 12-month lease and save on summer rent! Take over my furnished 1BR/1BA Ithacan Residences sublet until June 2025. Rent will range from $2000-2900/month depending on lease start date. Enjoy in-unit washer/dryer, stainless steel appliances, walk-in closet, and a flexible office space. Building boasts rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge, and more.
In-unit laundry. The apartment is located on the 8th floor, ensuring ample natural light as it's positioned above the adjacent parking garage.

ShortDescription: Beautiful Historical building. Apartments have hardwood floors, updated tiled kitchens and baths, free laundry and utilities included (heat, water, electricity) saving $100-200/month for each tenant.
LongDescription: This gorgeous 4-bedroom apartment is available June '25 thru May '26 as low as $875 per person. You will be steps from Collegetown and campus and seconds from the bus stop. ShortDescription: *1 room available* Penthouse 602 is a fully furnished, 4-bed 2-bath unit in the heart of Collegetown. On the top floor, it offers privacy, stunning views, in building washer/dryer, and fitness room.
LongDescription: Penthouse Apartment 602 at 205 Dryden Rd is a 4-bed, 2-bath fully furnished unit. Located on the top floor, it offers privacy, natural light, and excellent views. The spacious layout includes 4 furnished bedrooms (*1 available*), a living area, and modern finishes. The secure building has on-site laundry and is within short walking distance of Cornell University, restaurants, and shops in Collegetown. The sublet provides a desirable option for students seeking housing close to campus.

ShortDescription: Bedroom for rent, just 5 minutes from Cornell. Includes utilities and internet, with a small electricity charge. Furnished, shared kitchen and living room with students. Pets allowed with deposit.
LongDescription: A cozy private bedroom for rent, available right away! It’s just a quick 5-minute drive to Cornell and conveniently located near the bus stop. Rent included utilities, internet, and trash collection—just a small electricity charge applies. Pets are warmly welcomed with a deposit! Features furnished bedrooms, a spacious kitchen, a large living room, and a lovely backyard. You’ll share the space with fellow students, creating a friendly atmosphere. Plus, free street parking is available!

ShortDescription: Spring 2025 Sublet – 216 Delaware Ave, Ithaca, NY
LongDescription:
Hey everyone! I’m looking for a female subletter for my room in a spacious 4-bedroom, 2-bathroom apartment super close to campus. (NO HILLS) The room is fully furnished, and you’ll have awesome, friendly roommates!
Rent is $1,170 per month (utilities not included), however I’ll discount it to $600 a month. Move-in is flexible between January 10-20, so you can get settled before classes start. Feel free to message me if you’re interested or have a question! You can move in anytime after 1/10.

Contact me for more information!

ShortDescription: SUMMER 2025 SUBLET
LongDescription:
SUMMER 2025 SUBLET

Hello, I'm looking to sublet 1 to 4 rooms on 128 Blair Street from June 1 to August 17. Located centrally in Collegetown, the apartment is a 10 minute walk from Cornell, and a 15 minute walk from the Commons and Ithaca College.

Price:
$1050 per month + Utilities (Negotiable)

Amenities:
Internet included in rent 
Fully furnished 
Air conditioning 
Spacious kitchen and living room
Dishwasher 
Washer and dryer in unit 
Hardwood floors 
Large backyard 
Balcony porch

ShortDescription: Room available for sublet until May 18, 2025 in furnished Ithaca home, walking distance from Cornell's campus and Ithaca Commons. Renovated kitchen with stainless appliances, heat, A/C, and laundry.
LongDescription:
Sublet is for one beautifully furnished, light-filled bedroom and shared common space, including kitchen, living room, family room, dining room, and sunroom. Tall ceilings, classic Victorian details, formal entry, & Lodge-style sunroom. Distant views of West Hill from all three stories.

Wooden fencing encloses the backyard with stone patio and kitchen garden.

Email current Cornell graduate student at jab865@Cornell.edu.

Subject to landlord approval. Friendly dog on premises some of the time.

ShortDescription: Room available from March to May, just a 5-7 minute walk to Collegetown and Cornell via Hoy Road. Great location for students. The room shares a kitchen and bathroom with three housemates.
LongDescription:
Looking for someone to take over my lease from March to May. This cozy room is in an ideal location, just a 5-7 minute walk to Collegetown and conveniently close to Cornell University via Hoy Road—perfect for students or anyone visiting the university.

The room is on a shared floor with three other housemates. It features:

Three large windows overlooking the side yard with morning sunlight.
A shared kitchen and bathroom.
This is a great opportunity for anyone looking for temporary housing.

ShortDescription: Modern Studio Apartment in the Heart of Collegetown!
LongDescription:
Live steps from Cornell at 407 College Ave! This 4-bedroom, 2-bath apartment features spacious rooms and large windows for great natural light. Enjoy the convenience of on-site laundry, secure entry, and friendly management. With dining, shopping, and campus just outside your door, this prime Collegetown location is perfect for students and professionals. Don’t miss out—schedule a tour today!

**Rent is $5,675, not $5,000**

ShortDescription: 1 Bed in a 3x3 Bed TownHouse with Garage in Maplewood. All included. Available June and July.
LongDescription: I am looking for someone to transfer my Maplewood lease to for the summer. I currently live in a 3bedx3bath Townhouse (you get your own bathroom). Covers all utilities (including wifi) with in-unit washer/dryer. Parking is available for $135/month. The lease transfer would be effective 6/1 - 7/31 2025. You would have 2 female roommates during this time. One of my roommates has a male cat. 20 min walk (5 min drive) from campus. Fitness center, maintenance, and package room included.

ShortDescription: 2 story apartment in a duplex with 3 bedrooms and 1 bathroom. Short walk to Cornell, Commons, Lakefront
LongDescription: 2 story apartment in a duplex with 3bed+1bath. Downstairs includes open concept living room, dining room + kitchen with a built in island. ShortDescription: Beautiful recently renovated rental in a country setting, only 4 miles to Cornell
LongDescription:
Clean updated rental with lots of character, just a few miles from Cornell and downtown.  Excellent open floor layout, land, and amenities for memorable gatherings.  5 acre property is surrounded by woods and nature.

Kitchen has dishwasher, gas range, granite countertops.  All spaces freshly painted, new carpets in bedrooms, very clean.  Mudroom and sunroom.  Shared laundry room.  

Large workshop space with an interesting history attached to house, can potentially be worked into rental

ShortDescription: One Room in a 3-bedroom apartment available NOW! Message soon for opportunity to receive a discount!
LongDescription:
Looking for female to take over my lease! You will have two female roommates for the duration of the lease. 

Apartment Features:
• Spacious Living
• Furnished: The room comes fully furnished with a frame and mattress, wardrobe, desk & desk chair, coffee/dining table, dishwasher, microwave, sofa, flat screen TV, and more.

• Community Amenities: Fitness center, free and fast Wifi, passcode accessible mail room, public bus route access downstairs, private bus service for residents, parking

ShortDescription: Old House with high ceilings, bulit in 1902. Graduate Students preferred.  3 bedrooms for 3 unrelated tenants. It has two off-street parking. Quiet yet convenient location. real hardwood floors.
LongDescription: The apartment has 3 bedrooms for 3 unrelated tenants. It has two off-street parking space. New cooking stove, new furnace, new hot water boiler.  Laundry (washer and dryer) on site in basement for usage by tenants of the house only.  It is a rather rare unit in downtown, the same block with Gimme Coffee! Landlord lives in Florida but accessible via e-mail, internet. Apt-2 tenants can use huge attic space for extra storage. APT-2 has an attic, contributed to many thesis and dissertations.

ShortDescription: We are two third year PhD students in Social Sciences, looking for a roommate to share an apartment in the village of Cayuga Heights (north of Ithaca, Highland Road) for the 2025-2026 academic year.
LongDescription:
The apartment is very well located! It's just an 18-minute walk from campus, in a very quiet area. Two bus lines (32 and 30) have stops nearby. It's easy to get to campus, college town or downtown using either of these lines. Line 32 goes straight down to central campus in 7 minutes. There's plenty of on-street parking nearby if you have a car.
The apartment has a spacious kitchen and a fairly large living room with a TV and comfortable sofas. Cleanliness is a must for us.

ShortDescription: 572 Warren Rd. Quiet lg home on 2 acres.5min drive to Cornell and 2min walk to TCAT! Free parking. All-inclusive rent (utils, WiFi). Community printer and computer. Routine cleaning service.
LongDescription: Quiet furnished home @ 572 Warren Rd (~2 acres). 5min drive/2min walk TCAT to Cornell. Welcoming to all! Rms $665-850 (vary: size/bath/lease). Rent INCLUDES: ALL utils, high-speed WiFi, common area cleaning, free laundry, free parking, grounds maint, house computer/printer! Shared: well-equipped kitchen (2 fridges), 3 decks, living/dining rms, lounge & study areas. Contact us for a rental application!

ShortDescription: One bedroom apartment, entire first floor of duplex.  On bus line downtown, close to everything. Avail June or July.
LongDescription: Large bedroom, full bathroom, full kitchen, large living room. Private entry. Hardwood & ceramic tile flooring. Unfurnished. Avail 1st July for 12 mo lease, or move-in in June for 13 mo w reduced June rent. Tenant pays gas, electric, garbage, internet/cable. Legal for one person or couple. On bus route, close to many amenities: shopping, dining, entertainment. Curbside parking, & shared driveway. No smoking. Pet allowed upon review/approval, with non-refundable fee.

ShortDescription:
Available ~May 3 – August 9 (Flexible Dates!)

Fully furnished apartment just steps from the Commons and Six Mile Creek Trail. 1 bedroom + bonus room, private patio overlooking creek, new building.
LongDescription: Fully furnished summer sublet in Cayuga Lofts (981 sq ft), steps from Downtown Ithaca and Six Mile Creek Trail. 1BR + bonus room (no window, sliding door), private patio, modern layout. Available ~May 3–Aug 9 (flexible). Garage parking available for ~$90/month. Great for interns, students, or anyone looking for a quiet, central spot. Friendly staff, green building features, walkable to shops, cafes, and buses.
